Ad Text:
About the role
We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst to support the delivery of complex transformation and regulatory & compliance initiatives across our organisation. This role sits within the Transformation & Technology function and works closely with Product Owners, Delivery Leads and senior stakeholders to define, plan and deliver sustainable business outcomes.
  
The Senior Business Analyst will lead analysis activities across large and high-risk initiatives, often operating in environments with regulatory, compliance and operational complexity. This role requires strong planning capability, confidence engaging at executive level, and the ability to work effectively across both Agile and Waterfall delivery models.
  
Working as part of an inclusive and collaborative team your key responsibilities will include:
  

Lead end-to-end business analysis activities across complex initiatives
Operate effectively within Agile and Waterfall delivery environments
Plan and manage scope, dependencies, risks and deliverables
Engage and influence senior and executive stakeholders, including clear and concise written communication
Translate regulatory and compliance requirements into practical business and system solutions
Define and document business requirements, user stories and process models
Lead and coordinate testing activities, including UAT planning and execution
Identify and implement process improvement and automation opportunities
Provide coaching and mentoring support to other Business Analysts within the team
Contribute to continuous improvement of business analysis standards, tools and ways of working
  
  
What will you bring?

Significant experience as a Business Analyst delivering complex initiatives
Strong experience working across Agile and Waterfall methodologies
Demonstrated strength in planning, organisation and delivery management
Proven executive-level stakeholder management capability
Experience working within banking regulated and compliance-driven environments
Solid experience with testing and quality assurance activities
Experience delivering process improvement or automation initiatives
High standard of written and verbal communication
Experience with CRM platforms such as Dynamics or Salesforce
Exposure to UX/UI concepts, including wireframing is desirable
IIBA or equivalent business analysis certification is desirable


 
What we can offer you
There’s life at work, and life outside of work – and we understand that.
P&N Group is committed to creating a satisfying and fulfilling working environment, offering employee benefits and development opportunities that reward and help you perform to your potential and expand your experience and learning.

To help you live your best life through work, we offer an extensive range of employee benefits.

Work for a national multi-brand, customer-focused organisation
Enjoy flexible work arrangements
An incentive scheme for exceptional performance
Be supported with leadership and professional development
12 weeks paid parental leave for the primary care giver, and three weeks for the non-primary care giver
Generous discounts on home loans, personal loans, insurance and other banking products and services
Up to two weeks’ additional purchased leave per year
Two days’ paid volunteer leave each year to use with a community partner of your choice
An Employee Assistance Program
About us
P&N Group is amongst the largest customer-owned banking organisations in Australia, represented by P&N Bank in Western Australia and BCU Bank in New South Wales and southeast Queensland. Our purpose is to enrich the lives of our customers and their communities.
  
With over $9 billion in assets and a head office in Perth and corporate offices in Coffs Harbour and Brisbane, we service over 200,000 customers across Australia from all walks of life supported by over 600 employees in group services, retail banking, broker, and business banking roles.
  
We believe our culture is a real point of difference, and our values – Focus on Members, Improve & Learn and Trust & Collaborate – are fundamental to our ways of working. We offer a collaborative and inclusive workplace where our people feel a strong sense of belonging, are recognised, invested in, cared for, and are part of something bigger.
  
What does our recruitment process look like?
The process can include a phone screen, virtual and/or face-to-face interview, psychometric testing, reference checks and all relevant background checks.
At P&N Group, we want to leverage the numerous benefits and innovative gains that a diverse workforce brings, and especially the high engagement that comes from a culture built on belonging and inclusion. We encourage people of all abilities, backgrounds, identities, ages and cultures to apply.

If you need assistance or require flexibility to be able to fully participate in the application process, please email us at recruitment@pnbank.com.au

The closing date for applications is 21 January 2026

Ad Text:
Client


Our client has ambitious growth plans to double the business over the next 2–3 years, we are investing heavily in technology, data, and digital capability. The role is reporting directly to the Chief Information Officer (CIO), this is a senior, hands-on leadership role where you will guide both engineering and data functions, while remaining deeply involved in delivery.


About the role


You will lead direct reports across engineering and data, spending 60–70% of your time hands-on with code, architecture, and solution design. This role is ideal for a technical leader who enjoys working close to the detail while shaping strategy and driving change in a traditional business modernising at scale.


Key Responsibilities


Lead, mentor, and manage a team of engineers and data specialists
Remain hands-on with development, architecture, and solution delivery
Break down work, assign tasks, and manage team workload and priorities
Act as a key technical contact for external vendors delivering Microsoft Dynamics solutions
Develop and enhance customer portals for residential and commercial clients
Design and implement system integrations and APIs
Contribute to architectural decisions within the Microsoft ecosystem
Support AI initiatives and identify automation opportunities to drive efficiency

Required Skills & Experience


Strong full-stack development background
Deep experience with Microsoft technologies, including:

Microsoft Dynamics (Business Central & Customer Engagement)
Azure Cloud
.NET
React
Power BI
Proven experience building APIs and system integrations
Mobile and web application development experience
Experience leading and developing technical teams
Understanding of AI applications and automation opportunities
Experience working within medium to large organisations
Adaptable and comfortable working in a fast-changing environment
Strong collaborator with cross-functional stakeholders
Passionate about AI, automation, and continuous improvement
Exposure to multiple industries or complex business environments
Strong stakeholder and vendor management skills
Practical, solutions-focused mindset

Offer

Opportunity to shape technology strategy during a major digital transformation
Hands-on technical leadership in a business investing heavily in modern platforms
Competitive salary package
The chance to make a tangible impact in a business scaling rapidly
3 days on site 

For a confidential discussion please apply or reach out to Corin on 0457676048

Job Title: Lecturer or Senior Lecturer in Information Systems and Business Analytics
Salary: Multiple roles across Level B & Level C
Ad Text:
Based at our Melbourne, Burwood Campus
Multiple Full-time and continuing positions available
Level B $117,684 - $139,191 + 17% Superannuation or Level C $143,490 - $165,001 + 17% Superannuation

Why work with us? 

At Deakin you will have access to benefits such as a variety of leave options including generous parental leave and the ability to purchase additional leave; flexible working arrangements to help manage your work-life balance; ongoing learning and development opportunities to grow your career; an inclusive and supportive culture and environment to work in, both online and on campus.

Who are we?

The Faculty of Business and Law is committed to excellence in teaching, learning, and research, with a focus on creating positive social and economic impact. The School of Business prioritises solution-driven research and collaborates closely with industry and government to translate findings into practice. Within this, the Information Systems and Business Analytics (ISBA) group is a forward-thinking academic community applying AI, data analytics, and innovative digital technologies to shape the future of technology-enabled business and improve organisational performance.

About the role:

The role delivers high-quality, student-centred teaching across undergraduate and postgraduate programs while contributing to a dynamic research community. It involves leading unit teaching teams, designing innovative and inclusive curricula, and integrating industry and research insights into student learning. The role also conducts impactful research in areas such as AI, business analytics, and responsible digital technologies, and contributes to a culture of educational excellence and strong industry engagement.

As a Lecturer (Level B) or Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the School of Business, you will:

Lead unit and course teaching teams, working collaboratively across the faculty to develop effective curricula and learning materials, review units and courses, and implement evidence-based refinements.
Integrate industry, clinical and research practice into unit and course design to enhance student learning experiences, engagement, success and the relevance of learning resources.
Lead the development and adoption of innovative, learner-centric and research-informed curriculum design across a range of levels and delivery modes, including the creation of inclusive and collaborative learning opportunities.
Develop and moderate high-quality assessment tasks and rubrics at unit and course level, providing clear assessment criteria and timely feedback to demonstrate learning outcomes and strengthen student achievement.
Foster a culture of collaboration and educational excellence by supporting students, mentoring colleagues, building teaching and learning capability, and contributing to pedagogical research and scholarly practice.
               

To be successful, you’ll have:

PhD in Business Analytics, Information Systems or a related discipline, or equivalent relevant qualifications and experience.
Strong expertise in the area of effective use and responsible use of digital technologies, including AI, machine learning, business analytics, with a growing or established research track record with quality publications and/or external research funding
Excellent track record of high-quality teaching in AI, machine learning, business analytics at both undergraduate and postgraduate levels, including experience in innovative curriculum development and in supervising Honours and/or HDR students.
Capacity to contribute to research leadership, academic administration, and broader community engagement through impactful research.
Excellent interpersonal skills and a proven ability to build effective working relationships with colleagues.


Here's how to apply: 


Please submit your current academic curriculum vitae and a cover letter that clearly states which level and role you are applying for, and detailed responses to the Key Selection Criteria.

For a confidential discussion regarding this role, please contact Associate Professor Van-Hau Trieu, Discipline Chair, Information Systems and Business Analytics via t.trieu@deakin.edu.au

For a copy of the position descriptions, please see below:

 Level B - TRS Lecturer ISBA Nov2025_FINAL.pdf

 Level C - TRS Senior Lecturer ISBA Nov 2025_FINAL.pdf

Applications for this position close on Tuesday 20th January 2026.



Are You Ready?

Deakin is a Victorian university with a global impact. We are an agile, dynamic, and innovative university committed to making a positive impact through our excellence in education, research and innovation and the contributions we make to the wider community.
We understand that our reputation has been built on the dedication and expertise of our staff and we offer a dynamic and diverse working environment with opportunities to grow and develop careers. We believe that a progressive, thriving culture will ensure that people choose to come, and stay at Deakin and contribute to our ongoing success.
We value diversity and aim to build an inclusive environment that champions, embraces and respects differences. We support and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, and people of all abilities, cultures, sexual orientation, and genders.

Ad Text:
Employment Type: full time continuing role as a Portfolio Analyst – Benefits and Planning, UNSW IT
Starting salary $127351 plus generous super and leave loading
Location: UNSW Kensington Campus (Hybrid Working Opportunities) 2-3 days currently in the office

About UNSW:
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organization with a diverse and talented community, a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

UNSW IT is part of UNSW’s Operations Division and provides reliable, cost effective and state of the art IT services. The Division was established in recent years to provide corporate services in support of the Faculties and Divisions. As part of this change the UNSW IT team continues to evolve as it works toward its ambition of being a world class technology delivery and support team enabling the University with world class solutions and capabilities.

Portfolio Analyst – Benefits & Planning plays a key role within UNSW IT and the IT PMO, driving and managing project benefits and outcomes, whilst governing the process and toolset that facilitates annual portfolio planning.

The role entails the application of enterprise benefits management standards, working with project managers to ensure project benefits plans are achievable and measurable, and the development and maintenance of reporting that will enable periodic tracking of benefits and outcomes across the IT portfolio. The role also entails working closely with Heads Of and SME roles to capture, curate and report the source data which facilitates the prioritization and sequencing of the annual IT projects portfolio.

The role reports to the Head of Portfolio and Projects and has no direct reports.

Specific accountabilities for this role include:

Lead the UNSWIT portfolio benefits function, including the review of business cases, provision of advice to project managers, and entry and tracking of benefits and outcomes in UNSW’s project management toolset, Altus.
Work with the IT PMO Systems and Tools lead to develop benefits and outcomes reporting in Power BI.
Provision of quarterly benefits reporting through to various UNSW executive functions, including Council and UNSW EPMO.
Regular interaction with UNSW EPMO around benefits management, including the proposal of improvements to both the tooling and process.
Lead and govern submissions to UNSW IT’s portfolio planning tool, LEANIX, working closely with the Strategy & Architecture Directorate, and Domain representatives.
Co-facilitate UNSWIT’s annual portfolio planning process via the development of reports and insights based on data from LEANIX
Assist the Head Of Portfolio and Projects with Portfolio Steering Committee and Project Review reporting.
Assist the Head Of Portfolio and Projects to drive the IT PMO’s journey to a Hybrid PMO through the sharing of Agile experiences, tooling, templates and ways of working
Align with and actively demonstrate the Code of Conduct and Values
Ensure hazards and risks psychosocial and physical are identified and controlled for tasks, projects, and activities that pose a health and safety risk within your area of responsibility.

Skills and Experience:

Relevant tertiary qualification with subsequent relevant experience or equivalent competence gained through any combination of education, training and experience.
Minimum of 5 years relevant experience including demonstrated experience as a Benefits and/or Portfolio planning lead for a large, complex program or portfolio.
Knowledge of project management and reporting toolsets, including Altus (Project Online) and PowerBI
Proven experience in both Waterfall and Agile ways of working
End to End process re-engineering skills
Proven experience, with an in-depth understanding, of the project life cycle, including post project and strategic development of portfolio planning and roadmaps.
Sound interpersonal and communication skills, and proven ability to engage effectively with diverse stakeholders to achieve successful outcomes.
Demonstrated analytical and problem-solving skills and proven capacity to exercise initiative, flexibility and to be proactive in development of solutions to problems.
Advanced written and verbal communication skills, with a high level of attention to detail for deliverables produced.
Well-developed time management skills, with a demonstrated ability to respond to changing priorities, manage multiple tasks and meet competing deadlines by using judgement and initiative.
An understanding of and commitment to UNSW’s aims, objectives and values in action, together with relevant policies and guidelines.
Knowledge of health and safety responsibilities and commitment to attending relevant health and safety training.

To Apply: If this is of interest to you, please submit your CV, Cover Letter and responses to the Skills and Experience outlined above and in the position description.

More Information: visit https://www.jobs.unsw.edu.au/

Contact

Jen MacLachlan, email: j.maclachlan@unsw.edu.au

Applications close: Wednesday 7th Jan at 11.30pm

Benefits and Culture

Flexible hybrid working
Additional 3 days of leave over the Christmas Period
Access to lifelong learning and career development
Progressive HR practices
Discounts and entitlements 

UNSW is committed to equity diversity and inclusion. Applications from women, people of culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, those living with disabilities, members of the LGBTIQ+ community; and people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander descent, are encouraged. UNSW provides workplace adjustments for people with disability, and access to flexible work options for eligible staff.

The University reserves the right not to proceed with any appointment.

We are looking for someone who can lead senior business programs from the front of the room. This role combines stage hosting, panel moderation, keynote delivery and research preparation. You must be able to step into a room of executives, guide complex conversations, and extract meaningful insight without relying on scripts.

Core Responsibilities:

Event MCing

Host full day conferences and executive forums of 150 to 300 attendees.

Regular monthly domestic travel is required for event hosting across Australia.

Set the tone with structured opening remarks and keep the programme moving cleanly.

Manage transitions between keynote speakers, panels, firesides and breaks.

Handle timing, unexpected changes and speaker delays without disrupting the flow.

Panel Moderation

Moderate several panels per event with senior leaders across technology, operations, finance, risk, data or similar disciplines.

Prepare a discussion structure that pushes panellists beyond high level commentary.

Interrupt constructively, redirect when needed and draw out specific examples.

Keep panels focused, balanced and on schedule.

Fireside Interviews

Run one to three focused interviews each event with senior executives.

Lead conversations that reveal practical decisions, challenges and lessons.

Maintain a clear narrative arc that helps the audience follow and engage.

Keynote Segments

Deliver ten to fifteen minute framing segments that introduce themes and orient the audience.

Use research, data and industry signals to ground commentary.

Present confidently without relying on slides or dense decks.

Research and Content Preparation

Review surveys, interviews, past sessions and industry material to build talking points.

Produce briefing notes for panellists and interviewees, including angles, likely tensions, and practical questions.

Prepare segment scripts, segues, and transition lines that hold the event together.

Keep up to date on trends across technology, leadership, strategy, operations and transformation.

Pre Event Preparation

Meet with speakers and panellists to understand their background, preferred themes and boundaries.

Identify contrasting views that can make discussions more dynamic and useful.

Contribute to the event run sheet and overall content flow.

On Camera and Media

Host short recorded interviews for social or post event content.

Film intros, promotional snippets or recap segments when required.

Represent the organisation as a credible, neutral voice across formats.

Skill Requirements

Demonstrated experience as an MC, presenter, journalist, analyst or live moderator.

Minimum 3-5 years of professional experience in MC, presenting, journalism, analysis or live moderation is required.

Ability to understand complex topics quickly and translate them into structured conversations.

Confident, articulate stage presence with strong pacing and audience awareness.

Comfortable challenging senior voices respectfully and guiding conversations back on track.

Strong written skills for briefing notes, scripts and session framing.

Able to think on your feet, connect ideas live, and salvage weak answers without the audience noticing.

Who This Suits

Someone who enjoys leading rooms of senior professionals and is energised by live discussion.

Someone with a research or media background who can switch between preparation and delivery smoothly.

Someone who can balance authority and neutrality while keeping discussions sharp and practical.

Job Title: Principal Engineer - MQ-28 Global Digital Ecosystem
Ad Text:
The Opportunity

The Boeing MQ-28 - Ghost Bat is a globally significant program delivering disruptive advantage to support Defence operational capabilities. Developed in partnership with the Royal Australian Air Force, it is the first military combat aircraft to be designed, manufactured and assembled in Australia in 50 years. 

As MQ-28 expands internationally, the program requires robust, secure and export-compliant data architecture to manage and store data across multiple customer nations. 

Role overview

You will partner closely with the MQ-28 Global Digital Ecosystem Principal Engineer to define, implement and govern the MQ-28 enterprise data architecture and reference data platforms.  Your role will deliver on the digital architecture and solution patterns that enable global design collaboration for engineering design, flight test, maintenance, logistics and operational analytics.

Key responsibilities

Define and maintain the MQ-28 enterprise data architecture and data product roadmap in alignment with program strategic roadmaps and product architecture.
Design reference data platform architectures (cloud, hybrid, and on‑prem) to ingest, store, process and serve high‑volume flight test, telemetry, sensor and maintenance data at scale.
Specify data models, canonical schemas, ontologies and metadata standards to enable cross‑domain interoperability (engineering, operations, logistics, analytics).
Establish data governance, stewardship, cataloguing and lifecycle policies that incorporate export control, data rights, IP, and cross‑jurisdictional access constraints.
Define secure data integration and exchange patterns.
Develop architectures for efficient analytics and ML/AI workflows (data lakes, feature stores, data warehouses, MLOps pipelines) supporting test analysis, performance trending and predictive maintenance.
Create reference implementation patterns and reusable data platform blueprints for supplier/partner onboarding and rapid capability delivery.
Collaborate with security, export control, legal and compliance teams to ensure architecture meet export constraints and national security requirements.
Define interoperability contracts, APIs, data contracts and SLAs for internal systems and external partners/nations.
Lead data migrations, ingestion design and coexistence strategies for existing PLM/ALM/SE systems and new data platforms.
Produce architecture artefacts including data flow diagrams, logical & physical data models, data lifecycle diagrams, capacity & cost models and interface specifications.
Provide technical leadership and mentoring to data engineers, platform teams and stakeholders.
Communicate architecture rationale, risks, cost/benefit tradeoffs and timelines to program leadership and international partners.

Essential skills & experience

Proven experience as a Data Architect or Senior Data Engineering/Architecture role on complex, multi‑stakeholder defence, aerospace or mission‑critical programs
Expertise designing large‑scale data platforms: data lakes, data warehouses, streaming platforms, feature stores and analytical pipelines
Strong experience with cloud data architectures (AWS/Azure/GCP) and hybrid/on‑premises integration in regulated environments
Deep understanding of data modelling (relational, time-series, event-sourced), metadata, master data management and ontologies
Practical experience with ingestion and integration patterns (e.g. Kafka/streaming, ETL/ELT, CDC, APIs, message buses and batch processing)
Experience implementing data security controls and familiarity with cyber control frameworks (e.g. Essential 8, ISM, NIST800-43)
Familiarity with export control frameworks (ITAR/EAR or equivalents), data sovereignty requirements and contractual data/IP rights
Australian Citizenship (required for Defence security clearance). 

Desirable skills & experience

Hands-on with data platform technologies and tools such as AWS (S3, Glue, Kinesis, Redshift, SageMaker), Azure (Data Lake, Event Hubs, Synapse, ML), GCP (BigQuery, Dataflow), Kafka, Snowflake, Databricks, Postgres/TimescaleDB.
Familiarity with PLM/ALM/SE ecosystems and integrating engineering toolchains into data platforms.
Experience with observability, data lineage and catalog tools (OpenLineage, Amundsen, DataHub, Collibra).
Knowledge of ML/AI operationalisation, feature stores and MLOps practices.
Scripting and automation skills (Python, CI/CD tooling) to support prototype and reference implementations.
Prior exposure to global defence programs or multi‑national supplier networks. 

Other benefits

Work on cutting edge projects with opportunities to work across platforms
Attractive remuneration and annual bonus
Formal reward and recognition program
Access discounts for health insurance, travel and accommodation
Paid parental leave and Defence leave
Salary packaging options available
Health and wellbeing benefits include annual flu vaccinations and Employee Assistance Program
Social and community groups 

BDA works with strong links with our global Boeing community, and we strongly encourage collaboration with our international counterparts.

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace. Female applicants, people of Aboriginal or Torres Strait Island descent and veterans are encouraged to apply.

Please note, this role will be shortlisted in 2026. Your patience is appreciated.

About Our Client

Our client is a leader in delivering innovative SAP solutions across Australia. They are committed to helping organisations establish effective master data processes, governance models, and data quality frameworks. The team values collaboration, technical excellence, and continuous professional growth in a dynamic and supportive environment.

About the Role

As a Functional Consultant – MDG (Data), you will play a key role in designing, configuring, and implementing SAP Master Data Governance (MDG) solutions. You will deliver business solutions through design, build, and test phases, ensuring successful systems integration and client success.

Key Responsibilities:


Lead functional design, configuration, and deployment of SAP MDG for domains such as Business Partner, Customer, Vendor, Material, or Finance master data.
Facilitate blueprinting, process workshops, and solution design sessions aligned to SAP MDG and SAP S/4HANA best practices.
Translate business requirements into functional specifications for MDG data models, workflows, UI configuration, rules, and validations.
Support integration of MDG with SAP S/4HANA, ECC, CRM, SRM, and non-SAP systems using SOA, RFC, IDoc, and SAP Data Services.
Configure governance workflows, BRFplus rules, data replication frameworks, and mass processing functionalities.

Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

 

What you’ll be doing:

As the Senior Analyst - Operations Transformation, you’ll be the subject matter expert driving data-led transformation programs that shape the future of our airline operations. In this role, you will play a pivotal part in analysing labour performance,  and operational data to uncover and communicate insights, and identify opportunities to deliver efficiency, productivity and cost savings.

This position blends hands-on analysis with strategic program delivery, supporting Virgin Australia’s mission to build a more efficient, commercially focused, and engaged operation.

In addition you will:

Partner with key stakeholders across Virgin’s Operations team (Cabin Crew, Flight Crew, Airports, Engineering & Maintenance, and internal teams) to deliver transformation initiatives that lift productivity and operational efficiency.
Analyse workforce, productivity, financial and operational data to identify trends, opportunities, and improvement levers.
Build and model  scenarios that align labour supply with operational demand, supporting commercial and labour efficiency outcomes.
Develop clear, insight-driven recommendations and prepare high-impact presentations that communicate findings to senior leaders.
Support the design and delivery of transformation programs that improve performance, simplify processes, and enhance the frontline team experience.
Collaborate closely with Finance and People teams to validate assumptions, quantify benefits, and track productivity improvements.
Lead change and communication activities to ensure smooth implementation and adoption of new ways of working.
Contribute to EA planning and help drive the broader transformation agenda.
Monitor and report on program progress, highlighting risks, dependencies, and required interventions.

 

You’ll be great in this role if you:

Bring 3 - 4 years’ experience in analytics, corporate finance, commercial analysis, management consulting, or a transformation-focused environment.
Demonstrate strong analytical capability with the ability to interpret large, complex datasets and convert insights into practical, commercial recommendations.
Are highly skilled at preparing clear, concise presentations that tell a compelling story and influence decision-making.
Take ownership of a portfolio of transformation initiatives and drive them through to successful delivery.
Conduct robust research and analysis using internal and external data sources to support evidence-based decision making.
Confidently guide stakeholders and team members, where appropriate, through analysis and program delivery.
Consistently deliver high-quality outputs supported by strong commercial reasoning and quantitative insights.
Communicate clearly and professionally with senior stakeholders, providing structured materials and well-reasoned recommendations.
Proactively identify, assess, and manage risks and issues that may impact project delivery.

 

What you’ll get from us

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Heavily discounted air travel for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
Flexible working arrangements (including work hours and work from home)
Discounts on travel insurance, car hire, accommodation and experiences worldwide
Discounted Virgin Australia Lounge membership
Hospitality, retail, technology, beauty services and wellness discounts
Wellness support, including the betterme digital wellbeing platform
A comprehensive Employee Assistance Program, which offers confidential coaching and support from qualified professionals for all aspects of life – physical, mental, social and financial
Dress for Your Day – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever is appropriate for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you 

Equality rules

We’re all individuals. We love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.

Ready to apply?

We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.

Job Title: Dynamics 365 FO Functional Consultant - End User Training Specialist
Ad Text:
Dynamics 365 FO Functional Consultant
D365 FinOps Trainer / Product Specialist 

Sydney CBD base role
Hybrid or Onsite options

Full time permanent role 

Initially this role will have core focus on end-user training and user adoption. Over time this role with transition to a D365 F&O Product Owner Specialist position

  
About the Role
We are seeking an experienced Dynamics 365 Finance & Operations (F&O) Specialist to play an exciting end user training role in a major finance transformation project.  

This role will be instrumental during the go-live phase, ensuring successful user training, user adoption, and help with process alignment

Over time this role will may eventually transition into a D365 F&O PRODUCT OWNER position  
  
Key Responsibilities

Expert System Knowledge: Act as a subject matter expert on D365 F&O, leveraging its full range of features and capabilities.
End-User Training: Develop and deliver training sessions, work closely with accounting end users empowering staff to use D365 F&O effectively.
Drive User Adoption: Promote confidence and uptake of the system by end users across finance functions.
System & Process Challenge: Critically evaluate current workflows and suggest improvements that enhance efficiency and accuracy.
Testing & Validation: Assist with UAT (User Acceptance Testing) phase ensuring systems and processes meet business requirements.
Support the Go-Live Phase: Provide hands-on assistance during the critical implementation stage.

Skills & Experience

Proven experience with Microsoft Dynamics 365 Finance & Operations (F&O), particularly in finance modules.
Excellent ability to train and mentor end-users.
Analytical mindset with the ability to challenge systems and processes constructively.
Understanding of finance processes and their alignment with ERP systems.
Experience supporting system implementations and go-lives and/or UAT testing phases preferred
Only Sydney based candidates considered 
Desirable
Exposure to training, change management and user adoption strategies.
Relevant certifications in Dynamics 365 or finance systems ideal
